ploads/2025/04/gwenno@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/gwenno">Gwenno</a> has shared details of a new album called &#39;Utopia&#39;. Check out the hypnotic lead single &#39;Dancing On Volcanes&#39; and the newly shared live shows below.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/gwenno-mercury-prize-interview-manic-street-preachers-pipettes-indie-sleaze-3278237">Gwenno on working with Manics and the “debauchery” of “indie sleaze”</a><br /></strong></li></ul><p> The record is set to mark the fourth studio album from Gwenno and will be the follow-up to the critically acclaimed &#39;Tresor&#39;, which arrived in 2022 and earned a <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/mercury-prize-2022-shortlist-winner-explained-3277145">Mercury Prize nomination</a> . It is set for release on July 11 via Heavenly Recordings and is available to <a href="https://ffm.to/gwenno-utopia" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pre-order here.</a></p><p> According to the singer-songwriter, the album feels almost like a debut, as she uses the 10 songs on the tracklist to reflect on her journey so far, exploring a disaffected schoolgirl in Cardiff, a teenage dancer in Las Vegas, singer in indie pop group <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-pipettes">The Pipettes</a> and much more. Through exploring these memories, the album became centred on themes of self-determination and experimentation.</p><p> Today (April 7), Gwenno has shared the first preview of the LP with the lead single &#39;Dancing On Volcanoes&#39;. Over a swirling, nostalgia-driven backing track, the singer captures a sombre tone as she looks back on dancefloors that no longer exist. She both captures the sense of catharsis that came from being on the late-night dancefloor, as well as mourns an era that has passed.</p><p> “ <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jarvis-cocker">Jarvis Cocker</a> dancing alone on stage, surrounded by dry ice, perfectly conveying the loss of our congregational dancing and drinking in small venues with a slight swing of the hip and flick of a hand,” she explained. “Dancing &#39;til 5am at Le Mandela restaurant in Grangetown, Cardiff… the <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/pet-shop-boys">Pet Shop Boys</a> &#39; perfectly aimed observations on modern life… the spirit of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/johnny-marr">Johnny Marr</a> on guitar, his echoes of the Celtic sea passed down through the generations… the need to dance as a cathartic act… it&#39;s all here – Dancing on Volcanoes!”在下面查看。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="GWENNO - DANCING ON VOLCANOES" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ilBQpl0rmtg?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> As for the album as a whole, &#39;Utopia&#39; is Gwenno&#39;s first album recorded predominantly in English, and is expected to present a new side to both her life and songwriting.</p><p> “I feel as if I&#39;ve written a debut record, because it&#39;s a different language and it&#39;s a different part of my life. It&#39;s about that point where I go out into the world on my own, which people generally write about first, and then get on with their lives,” she said. “But it&#39;s taken me so long to digest it — I needed 20 years just to make sense of things, and I realised the starting point of my creative life isn&#39;t Wales, it&#39;s actually North America.”</p><p> “Everything&#39;s a diary entry for me. And in writing about all of this I&#39;ve remembered the chaos of myself,” Gwenno continued. “You get to this point and you go &#39;God, that quarter of a century went fast.&#39; But I want to acknowledge it, and respect it and say, for better or worse, all of that happened.”</p><p> Later this year, the singer will play a handful of live shows across the UK, including a slot in London later this month, as well as a slot with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/alanis-morissette">Alanis Morissette</a> in Cardiff and an appearance at <a href="https://www.nme.com/festivals/green-man">Green Man</a> Festival.</p><p> <a href="https://ticketmaster-uk.tm7559.net/c/2862475/431519/7559?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.co.uk%2Fgwenno-tickets%2Fartist%2F1914119" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit here</a> for tickets, and find a list of shows below. </p><figure id="attachment_3852428" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3852428" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3852428" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000.jpg" alt="Gwenno 'Utopia' album artwork" width="2000" height="2000" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000-400x400.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000-800x800.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000-696x696.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000-1392x1392.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/gwenno-album@2000x2000-1068x1068.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3852428" class="wp-caption-text"> Gwenno &#39;Utopia&#39; album artwork. CREDIT: Press</figcaption></figure><h2> <strong>Gwenno&#39;s 2025 live shows are:</strong></h2><p><strong>四月</strong><br /><strong>26 – London, The Social</strong></p><p><strong>可能</strong><br /><strong>04 – Salford, Sounds From The Other City</strong></p><p><strong>六月</strong><br /><strong>19 – Cornwall, The Lost Gardens</strong></p><p><strong>七月</strong><br /><strong>02– Cardiff, Blackweir Park (with Alanis Morisette)</strong></p><p><strong>八月</strong><br /><strong>16 – Crickhowell, Green Man Festival</strong></p><p><strong>十月</strong><br /><strong>31 – London, EartH</strong></p><p><strong>十一月</strong><br /><strong>11 – Cardiff, New Theatre</strong></p><p> In other Gwenno news, earlier this year the singer-songwriter <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/gwenno-and-redolent-announced-as-independent-venue-week-2025-ambassadors-3817928">acted as ambassadors for the 2025 edition</a> of <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/independent-venue-week">Independent Venue Week</a> alongside <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/redolent">rEDOLENT</a> . It took place between January 27 to February 2, and included hundreds of live shows across the UK.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/gwenno-announces-new-album-utopia-with-nostalgic-single-dancing-on-volcanoes-3852427">Gwenno announces new album &#39;Utopia&#39; with nostalgic single &#39;Dancing On Volcanoes&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
